This paper is about text summarization, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper discusses incorporating user preferences into text summarization, which is a common topic in the NLP community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses using machine learning techniques to generate summaries, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses incorporating topics and entities into the summaries, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses using a sequence-to-sequence framework, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
